Registry_createIsolatedAccount
├── When caller is owner
│   ├── Given address is owner address
│   │   ├── Given account is the first account
│   │   │   ├── It should create an isolated account.
│   │   │   ├── It should set the `accountCount` to 1.
│   │   │   └── It should mint the account token to the owner address.
│   │   └── Given account is not the first account
│   │       ├── It should create an isolated account.
│   │       ├── It should increment the `accountCount`.
│   │       └── It should mint the account token to the owner address.
│   └── Given address is zero address
│       └── It should revert.
│           └── With error `Registry__ZeroAddress` error.
└── When caller is not owner
    └── Given address is not zero address
        ├── It should create an isolated account.
        └── It should mint the account token to the given address.

